 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 16: THE KNOWLEDGE GRAPH IS THE KNOWLEDGE. Knowledge is not entities or datoms — it is the CONNECTIONS between them. An isolated INV is opinion. An INV connected to a test (witness) connected to source (trace) connected to a task (routing) connected to an outcome (hypothesis) IS knowledge. F(S) measures connection graph density. Every metric braid computes is a measurement of connection quality. THE CONNECTION LIFECYCLE: (1) BIRTH — proposed by trace scanner, acquisition function, or harvest. Low confidence. (2) ACTIVATION — agent interacts (follows recommendation, confirms witness, commits observation). Evidence accumulates. (3) STRENGTHENING (Hebbian) — co-activated connections strengthen. Same-command=1.0, same-session=0.5, adjacent-session=0.25. Fire together wire together. (4) CALIBRATION (Bayesian) — hypothesis ledger updates posterior confidence from prediction outcomes. 10 activations with 8 confirmations → confidence 0.8. (5) DECAY — unused connections weaken. 0.9^sessions temporal decay. Source entity changes → staleness signal → faster decay until re-verified. (6) DEATH — sustained zero confidence. Remains in store (C1 append-only) but contributes nothing. Resurrectable if new evidence appears. THREE FORCES: Hebbian growth (fast/per-session), Bayesian calibration (medium/per-phase), Structural discovery (slow/per-domain, Phase E). DEEPEST INSIGHT: The six ATT-0 schema attributes are not for context blocks — they are CONNECTION LIFECYCLE attributes. presentation-count=activation count, last-presented=last activation, hebbian-boost=co-activation accumulator, learned-weight=Bayesian posterior, calibration-count=update count, block-label=connection kind. EVERY connection type (witness, trace, hypothesis, attention) should carry these six attributes. One schema. One lifecycle. One learning dynamic. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-025, ADR-FOUNDATION-028, ADR-FOUNDATION-024."
